 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vaeldayanie>vaeldayanie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/13/02 4:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> back to the spells</span><hr size=1> I would like to see sony implement some type of quests for our class defining spells, like they did for the ice comet runes.  They could even make involved quests utilizing research, btw we are supposed to be good at that anyway.  Make the runes drop off some tough (non uber guild) mobs, but make the research relatively trivial at 200. the spell and runes should be no drop so we dont see either in the bazaar.<br>
<br>
I believe very strongly that uberwizards in uberguilds should not be the only ones to get the spells that are necessary to bring balance to our class.  The big problem right now is that our damage is tied almost exclusively to our spells.  Everyone else gets help from pets or some other source in doing damage.  Mele damage is controlled by their weapons.  <br>
<br>
I would say that with my spell book like it is, I am a hollow wizard.  I am like a warrior running around with a Centi Short sword and a set of crafted.  If I can ever get a SS drop maybe i will be like a warrior with a lammy instead.  <br>
<br>
Balancing the distribution of these spells would make wizards more desirable in groups, solving that problem as well.  I am not saying to give these spells away, make us earn them, but at least make getting them a possibility and stop giving their equivalents away to other classes.<br>
<br>
Vaeldayanie<br>
Sorcerer<br>
The Rathe<br>
Vengeance of Lost Souls <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=804.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=804.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=804.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a> <b>4</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=804.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=804.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=804.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=804.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=804.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=804.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="r